search(Searchable<T>) - Method in class algorithms.search.BFS
This method used to operate the search action according to the BFS algorithm is happens by using two lists - Open List - which contain the possible neighbors of every stage, sorting by the priority, and Close list - which contains the current state of every stage.
search(Searchable<T>) - Method in class algorithms.search.DFS
This method used to operate the search action according to the DFS algorithm is happens by operate another method - the algDFS - a recursive method which execute the search by the DFS alg.

Searchable<T> - Interface in algorithms.search
This interface define the common functions of the problems(/games) which can be solved by search algorithm Every problem has a Start State and Goal State, and by the algorithm, the player will get, by finite number of steps, from the Start to the Goal
